TASK 03: PROMPTING FOR TASK AUTOMATION
OBJECTIVE

To apply prompt engineering techniques for automating real-world tasks such as summarizing notes, extracting structured data, and transforming information into different formats.

TASK CHOSEN: NOTE SUMMARIZATION
AUTOMATION PROMPT

Act as a professional note summarizer.

Read the provided text carefully.
Identify the main ideas and important details.
Generate a summary in 5 bullet points.
Keep the language simple and concise.
Limit the summary to 100 words.
INPUT–OUTPUT EXAMPLE 1
INPUT

Artificial Intelligence (AI) is transforming industries worldwide. It helps automate repetitive tasks, improves decision-making, and increases efficiency.

OUTPUT
AI is transforming industries worldwide.
It automates repetitive tasks.
AI improves decision-making.
It increases efficiency.
AI is widely used across sectors.
INPUT–OUTPUT EXAMPLE 2
INPUT

Cloud computing allows users to access computing resources over the internet while reducing infrastructure costs.

OUTPUT
Cloud computing provides online resources.
It reduces infrastructure costs.
It improves scalability.
Data can be accessed remotely.
It supports flexible operations.
INPUT–OUTPUT EXAMPLE 3
INPUT

Digital marketing uses social media, search engines, and email to promote products and services.

OUTPUT
Digital marketing promotes products online.
Social media helps increase reach.
Search engines attract customers.
Email improves customer engagement.
Businesses generate more leads.
PROMPT ITERATION AND DEBUGGING
INITIAL ISSUE

The first version of the prompt generated summaries with inconsistent lengths and formats.

IMPROVEMENT MADE

Specific instructions were added regarding:

Number of bullet points
Word limit
Output format
RESULT

The generated summaries became more consistent, structured, and reliable.

REFLECTION

Prompt engineering improves task automation by providing clear instructions and constraints. Well-designed prompts ensure consistency, accuracy, and efficiency while reducing manual effort.

CONCLUSION

This task demonstrated how prompt engineering can automate note summarization effectively. Clear objectives, formatting requirements, and constraints help AI consistently produce concise and useful summaries
